DURBAN - The High Court in Pretoria yesterday sentenced a 23-year-old man to three terms of life imprisonment for rape, North West police said.
Lieutenant Colonel Pelonomi Makau said Ephraim Mokobane was sentenced on charges including rape, sexual assault, kidnapping and the possession of an unlicensed firearm.

“Mokabane was sentenced to three terms of life imprisonment for three counts of rape, another 30 years for three counts of rape, 18 years for nine counts of kidnapping, 15 years for robbery with a firearm, 30 years for two counts of robbery with aggravating circumstances, five years for pointing a firearm, five years for the unlawful possession of a firearm, and two years for two counts of compelling a minor to witness a sexual act, as well as a year for violation through a sexual act,” she said.
He was arrested on August 15 2016 for committing these offences between 2013 and 2014 at Skierlik, Centreville and Block F, all in the precinct of Letlhabile township near Brits. 
- African News Agency (ANA)